	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Images tend to go 404 rawther rapidly, so I'll make an ASCII art diagram.
<br />
<br /><strong>NES lockout chip defeater by Honeybee, found in an unlicensed Famicom to NES adapter<br />ASCII diagram by Damian Yerrick</strong>
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;4700 pF<br />NES35 o------&#41;|-----.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; |<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 1K&nbsp; &nbsp; |<br />&nbsp; VCC o------/\/\/--+----.<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 5.1K&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &#40;not E12&#41;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; |<br />CHR10 o--+--/\/\/---+--|/<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;|&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; |&nbsp; |\&gt;--o GND<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;| 2000 pF&nbsp; |<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;`----||----+-------o CIC10<br /></div>
<br /><ul><li>VCC: +5V, NES pin 36 </li><li>NES35: NES pin 35 </li><li>CHR10: CHR A10, Famicom pin 53 </li><li>CIC10: CIC pin 10 </li><li>GND: NES pin 72, CIC pin 12 </li></ul>
<br />Apparently the CHR10 connection is supposed to do something similar to the line from the Camerica mapper that "fools the lockout chip into attempting to communicate."
<br />
<br />Bregalad: What sizes of capacitors were used?  And how reliable is this lockout defeat?
<br />
<br />EDIT: updated with capacitance values.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


