	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Oops, I've forgettend the capacity values. The non-polarised cap in series with the 5.1kOhm resistor is 2nF (it's written 203 on it), and the polarised one next to the NES pin 35 is, I think, 4,7 nF (it's written 47-35 on it, normally there is only 3 digits, but I think the 5 stand for +/- 5% or something).
<br />
<br />Yes, it's accurate, but sometimes the NES power light turns itself on and off (the TV syncrinisation also does turn on and off). I don't think if it's because of the lockout chip or because of the bad connections trough the adaptator. If it's because of the lockout chip, the reliability is 66%, else it's nearly 100%

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


